hesion and that ds 3 and 1 are involved.","dimension":9,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.056391,0.093366,0.099578,0.10386,0.099724,0.09525,0.092542,0.085987,0.079748,0.072381,0.0645,0.056675],"unified_progress":[0.051334,0.083304,0.094131,0.10023,0.10148,0.099782,0.095886,0.091339,0.087639,0.077115,0.065306,0.052453]},{"section":6,"text":"Hmm, blisters that start in the mouth... that makes me think of mucosal involvement, which is common in some autoimmune bullous diseases.","dimension":17,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037418,0.089543,0.10272,0.12196,0.10146,0.095977,0.093044,0.087907,0.080265,0.073748,0.063115,0.052843],"unified_progress":[0.03272,0.070016,0.089671,0.10203,0.10316,0.10261,0.10323,0.098862,0.093499,0.087589,0.06913,0.047477]},{"section":7,"text":"The fact that the skin peels off with pressure suggests something related to the skin's structural integrity.","dimension":12,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042055,0.06897,0.084508,0.095644,0.099602,0.1,0.10047,0.09704,0.092597,0.08461,0.073769,0.060735],"unified_progress":[0.033816,0.063237,0.08072,0.091712,0.099297,0.10173,0.10153,0.10122,0.098627,0.093148,0.077579,0.057394]},{"section":8,"text":"The dermatologist mentioned ds 3 and 1.","dimension":6,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034286,0.062081,0.078701,0.087172,0.096212,0.098861,0.098293,0.096992,0.09359,0.095054,0.08387,0.074888],"unified_progress":[0.035693,0.065773,0.079768,0.090978,0.095774,0.096488,0.099289,0.097244,0.095815,0.09473,0.081917,0.06653]},{"section":9,"text":"I'm not entirely sure what that refers to, but I think it might be about the layers of the skin.","dimension":17,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03314,0.071301,0.087241,0.097159,0.096536,0.096022,0.095805,0.094511,0.091485,0.091269,0.07929,0.06624],"unified_progress":[0.030923,0.064747,0.081975,0.094048,0.098689,0.098972,0.10263,0.10098,0.098217,0.096035,0.077938,0.054845]},{"se